  "title": "Selbstbeschreibung",
  "story": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "1ad2df5b3d090fc4",
      "text": "By \"self-description\" we want to mean the production of a text or functional equivalents of a text (for example, indexical expressions such as \"we\" or \"here\" or a proper name) by which and through which the organization identifies itself. The text need not exist as a quasi-biblical, canonical document; but whatever fulfills the function of self-description must meet certain requirements of self-reference at the level of the system. It must span and unite quite different situations, occasions, circumstances by identity of reference, must always denote \"the same thing\" as being constant over time, but at the same time be flexible as far as meaning is concerned."
